  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A Requirement node mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis output comparison; however, the supporting ValidationResult was generated by a numerical-simulation activity. The package narrative frames the high-fidelity simulation sweep as functionally equivalent to bench-top experimental validation, but the structured activityType field disagrees with the requiredVerificationMethod, instantiating a W-AR-03 inference-method mismatch.",
