    "name": "Hemolysis output verification requirement",
    "description": "For a Class III device at MRL 5, hemolysis index predictions must be verified against physical bench measurements. The required verification method is experimental-validation: at least three independent flow-loop experiments spanning the five target operating points must confirm model outputs within ±15% of measured normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values before the model may be used as the primary regulatory basis.",
