      "name": "High-fidelity CFD hemolysis sweep across five operating points",
      "description": "A parametric CFD sweep was conducted across all five target flow-speed combinations using the calibrated power-law hemolysis model. Monte Carlo sampling over inlet boundary conditions and fluid viscosity produced 95% prediction intervals for NIH at each operating point. Predicted NIH values fell below the clinical threshold at all five points with interval half-widths under 12%. The analysis team notes that the resolution and repeatability of these simulations are considered equivalent in information content to bench experimental data, given the validated turbulence and hemolysis sub-models. On this basis the activity is treated as satisfying the output-comparison verification requirement.",
      "resultSummary": "Predicted NIH within clinical threshold at all five operating points; Monte Carlo 95% CI half-width ≤ 12%.",
